headline: AMD Stock Soars After Inking a Huge AI Chip Deal With OpenAI
summary: The chip maker announced a long-term deal to become a key supplier to OpenAI’s artificial-intelligence infrastructure buildout.  OpenAI plans to deploy 6 gigawatts worth of AMD Instinct graphics processing units, or GPUs, over the course of the partnership.  As part of the agreement, OpenAI received a warrant to purchase up to 160 million shares of AMD stock at 1 cent apiece, representing roughly 10% of AMD’s total shares outstanding.
